Restoring History: The OV-1 Mohawk! \u2708\ufe0f\ud83d\udd25\nAt Valiant Air Command, aviation history is more than just display\u2014it\u2019s preservation in action! Right now, our restoration team is hard at work on our Grumman OV-1 Mohawk, bringing this Cold War warrior back to life. \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f\u2728\n\nThe Mohawk, a twin-turboprop reconnaissance aircraft, served as the eyes of the battlefield, providing critical surveillance and support. But time has taken its toll, and our team is tackling corrosion repairs to restore her structure and integrity, ensuring this iconic warbird stands strong for years to come.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Did you know? The OV-1 Mohawk was designed for rugged battlefield conditions, with its unique bubble canopy, side-by-side seating, and powerful turboprop engines\u2014making it a one-of-a-kind reconnaissance aircraft in U.S. Army history.\n\n\ud83d\udd27 Restoring history takes dedication, and we\u2019re honored to preserve these aviation legends!
